<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-29T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-29T17:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11 Shanghai/14: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to">Cunningham</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-29T17:00:00-05:00">February 29, 1932—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>61. Your 100, February 23, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Refrain from including the clause until otherwise
                                instructed.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Department desires, however, to impress upon you and through you
                                upon the American nationals concerned the importance of obtaining,
                                while the evidence is fresh, complete and accurate evidence with
                                respect to any damages suffered by American nationals. This
                                information should indicate the nature and extent of the damage and
                                by whom it was caused, care being taken in connection with this
                                latter point to avoid the possibility of any effort on the part of
                                the contending factions to shift responsibility.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>